You can add the following to WlanApi.cs


public bool BackgroundScanEnabled
            {
                get
                {
                    return GetInterfaceInt(Wlan.WlanIntfOpcode.BackgroundScanEnabled) != 0;
                }

                set
                {
                    SetInterfaceInt(Wlan.WlanIntfOpcode.BackgroundScanEnabled, value ? 1 : 0);
                }
            }

After a successful connection I disable the background scanning.  Background scanning seems to enable itself after a disconnect.
